    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The current algorithm only looks at the 4 preceding the cursor and if they are all spaces, then 4 spaces are deleted.  This logic is applied regardless of where the cursor is located.  I am not convinced we want to change this as it would make the logic run on every backspace more complex.  But if you want to try to implement it and see if that logic can be made very clean, it might be worth it.\n"
